headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores 30, Bulls defeat Pistons 126-108 in Paris

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Al Horford’s 7-year-old, Ean, sat in the front row of the postgame news conference, wearing a hat from last season’s NBA Finals.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics beat Warriors in OT, win NBA Finals rematch 121-118

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell scored 16 of his 25 points in the fourth quarter, Anthony Edwards had 23 and the Minnesota Timberwolves rallied to beat the Toronto Raptors 128-126 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell scores 16 points in 4th, Wolves beat Raptors 128-126

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson got an All-Star level ovation from the home crowd in the first quarter when he came to the scorer's table, returning to the floor after losing 37 games to a knee injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mikal Bridges scores 28 points, Suns beat Nets to snap skid

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored 32 points and the Philadelphia 76ers stretched their winning streak to four games, all on the road, with a 105-95 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has 32, 76ers top Blazers 105-95 for 4th straight win
